# Ride Cancellation Prediction

This project explores ride cancellation prediction using machine learning techniques.

## Project Status
This project is still in progress.  
At this stage, the repository is organized to present two different analytical approaches for supervisor review and feedback.

## Problem Statement
Ride cancellations can affect both customer experience and operational efficiency.  
The aim of this project is to investigate the factors related to ride cancellations and explore predictive modeling approaches.

## Project Approaches

### Approach 1 — Baseline Model
This approach represents the initial analytical pipeline and includes:
- Data cleaning
- Exploratory data analysis (EDA)
- Initial modeling

Path: notebooks/approach_1

### Approach 2 — Enhanced Approach
This approach extends the initial pipeline and includes:
- Data cleaning and audit
- Feature engineering
- EDA and business insights

Path: notebooks/approach_2

## Purpose of This Repository
The current repository structure is intended to:
- present the two approaches clearly
- organize notebooks in a readable way
- support project development
- make it easier to receive academic feedback

